name: Slow Tide

reviews.review_text:
My experience at Slow Tide was nothing short of exceptional. We had a lunch event for twenty three people and I must share that all of us described it as “a mind-blowing experience”.
Everything was top notch. Fresh, original and creative food and beverage preparations. Excellent and truly gourmet. The ambience and views - stunning. The table setting - sophisticated and tasteful. The service- experienced and attentive. I could not have made a better selection and I cannot thank the team enough for making it so memorable and special for all of us.
Slow Tide is a restaurant to be proud of. Kudos to the Owner, Chef, and the entire team.

My time at Slow Tide was quite good until it wasn't. The restaurant sits snugly overlooking the Anjuna Beach with plenty of open space, natural decor, and a lovely bar counter. The cocktails, the appetisers, and the atmosphere were all good and amazing. A few of the waitstaff were very friendly and polite.

The part I did not like:  That morning, I called them to make a dinner reservation to celebrate our anniversary. I was informed that it was first come, first serve (probably because we were a couple). That evening, we were seated below the deck but (when I spotted an empty table and asked for it) we were moved to the upper deck. The waitstaff did inform us that we MAY have to give up our table as it was reserved for a party of four. (I have to note here that there were plenty of empty tables with high chairs. I chose not to sit in one of those as they give me a back ache.) A couple of drinks and appetisers later, just when we were about to order the main course, we were asked to vacate the table. I felt it was rather impolite of them as we were still eating. Reluctantly, while vacating the table, I expressed my displeasure with one of the waitstaff. Surprisingly, he was quite condescending and rude. Obviously, we didn't want to resume our dinner and left the place dissatisfied.
All this displeasure could have been avoided had they simply reserved a table for us.

Came across this place by chance and lucked out. Later got to know it’s really trending. The parking is about 200-300m before the shack if you want to park for free. If not, you can pay 200rs and park right outside. It’s a narrow road and I’m sure it gets busy.

The view is amazing. Slow tide is right at the beach. Reggae was playing and was quite pleasant. They seem to take reservations. They have a large space and an interior dining area too.

We ate -

• Fish thali - brilliant, leaf wrapped small fish fillet, little crab, prawns, fish fritters, potato sabzi, small sol kadi, rice, halwa etc 5/5

• Jaffna prawns - tiger prawns in a yummy masala with a string appam 5/5

• veg multigrain sandwich with sweet potato chips - my vegetarian friend was elated 5/5

• Bobby and the Bee cocktail - nice 4/5

• acid Eric - 5/5

• Chandra and Sandra - fine 4/5

• jig fizz - 5/5

We paid through Zomato and got a slight discount. Super happy with our experience. We paid about 1200 pp.

description:
### Slow Tide: A Culinary Haven in Anjuna

Nestled along the tranquil shores of Anjuna, **Slow Tide** has quickly established itself as a dining gem, boasting a commendable rating of **4.5** from a robust **662** reviews. Celebrated for its focus on **Goan food**, vibrant **thalis**, and incredible **beach** views, this restaurant promises an unforgettable culinary experience against the backdrop of stunning sunsets.

### Ambiance & Design

Walking into Slow Tide, you are greeted by an airy, open space decorated with natural elements that resonate with its beachside locale. The decor is simple yet elegant, with soft, ambient lighting that enhances the relaxed vibe while allowing the spectacular ocean views to take center stage. Various reviews highlight soothing sounds of reggae wafting through the air, creating a laid-back atmosphere perfect for a leisurely meal. The outdoor seating provides proximity to the beach where diners can savor their food while gazing out over the water, making for an idyllic setting.

### Menu & Culinary Experience

The menu at Slow Tide is a celebration of local flavors, showcasing fresh ingredients and culinary creativity. Signature dishes mentioned by customers include the **Fish Thali**, an assortment of expertly prepared seafood components that is described as “brilliant”; its presentation featuring a leaf-wrapped fish fillet and a delightful crab offering highlights the kitchen's attention to detail. Additionally, the **Jaffna Prawns** in a flavorsome masala served with a string appam received high praise for their bold flavors.

Vegetarians won’t be disappointed either, as noted in a review mentioning a highly-rated **Veg Multigrain Sandwich** accompanied by sweet potato chips—an option that left a plant-based diner "elated." Other notable mentions include unique cocktails like the refreshing **Bobby and the Bee** and the intriguing **Acid Eric**, perfectly complementing the culinary offerings. With dishes cleverly made to cater to various dietary preferences, Slow Tide is a place where every palate finds satisfaction.

### Customer Experience & Service

While the culinary delights often steal the spotlight, customer service at Slow Tide has received mixed reviews. Generally described as experienced and attentive, some visitors encountered inconsistencies in service, particularly regarding reservation management and table assignments, leading to moments of dissatisfaction. One guest recounted a frustrating experience after being asked to vacate their table prematurely, illustrating potential areas for improvement in communication and customer care. The blend of friendly service with challenging scenarios hints at a restaurant in transition, eager to refine the guest experience further.

### Popularity & Reviews

With a steady stream of positive feedback, Slow Tide is already trending among locals and tourists alike. Its picturesque location, combined with the appeal of a genuine Goan dining experience, has set social media abuzz, with photos of breathtaking sunsets and creatively presented dishes shared widely. Patrons often mention the reasonable pricing, claiming satisfaction even when dining with groups, and many have expressed eagerness to return despite minor service hiccups.

### Utilizing Visual Content

The visual allure of Slow Tide is undeniably reflected in the customer-provided photos. Images showcasing vibrant, well-plated dishes highlight the culinary artistry; diners can almost taste the seafood delicacies through the screen. The inviting outdoor seating with an ocean view captures the restaurant's essence, inviting new visitors to relax and enjoy a hearty meal by the beach. From the sophisticated table settings to the aesthetic cocktail presentations, it's clear that Slow Tide places a strong emphasis on the overall dining experience.

### Conclusion

Slow Tide presents a compelling blend of exquisite food, stunning views, and a vibrant ambiance that makes it a must-visit when in Anjuna. While there are aspects requiring attention, particularly regarding service consistency, the restaurant's dedication to quality and customer satisfaction shines through. As the sun sets over the beach, there's no better place to enjoy the taste of Goa—both in the dishes served and the memories created.
